Package: floweR
Type: Package
Title: Draws flower pictures
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Enrico Manlapig
Maintainer: Enrico Manlapig <emanlapig@westmont.ed>
Description: This package provides a function to draw simple flower shapes from a dataframe. The function draws one flower for each value of a grouping variable.  The length of each petal is mapped from a numeric variable.  Petal colors can also be mapped to a variable. Petals curvature and angle can be adjusted but cannot be mapped.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    dplyr, 
    ggplot2, 
    tidyr, 
    rlang
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
